      "rationale": "The primary QoI (relative hemolysis index RH) directly maps to the clinical acceptance criterion (RH < 1 versus predicate device). Secondary QoIs (shear stress distribution, exposure time) are mechanistically linked to red blood cell damage through the power-law hemolysis model. QoI selection reviewed and approved by clinical advisory board (memo CAB-2023-12)."
