    "actor": "https://uofa.net/morrison/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment for COU1 (CPB hemolysis prediction, MRL 2) is accepted based on the following structured evidence: (1) All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels for MRL 2, with discretization error exceeding requirements at achieved level 3. (2) The 6 scoped-out factors are appropriately excluded at MRL 2 with documented procedural controls and qualitative justifications. (3) Validation results demonstrate CFD predictions within ±10% of experimental measurements across all 5 operating points, with no systematic bias identified in Bland-Altman analysis. (4) The primary acceptance criterion (RH < 1 versus predicate device) is met at all operating points with margin. (5) Provenance chain is complete: all validation results link to experimental datasets, generating activities, and uncertainty quantification records. (6) The model risk level 2 designation is consistent with medium model influence and high decision consequence per ASME V&V 40 Table 3. The assessment team concludes that the CFD model has sufficient credibility for the stated COU and that the simulation evidence supports regulatory submission.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
